'''白厅的海伍德男爵傑里米·約翰·海伍德''' {{Post-nominals|country=GBR|GCB|CVO}}（{{lang-en|Jeremy John Heywood, Baron Heywood of Whitehall}}，{{bd|1961年|12月31日|2018年|11月4日|catIdx=Heywood}}），英國高級[[英國文官隊伍|公務員]]，曾兩度擔任[[首相私人秘書長|首相私人秘書長]]、一任[[唐寧街幕僚長|唐寧街幕僚長]]，“唐寧街[[常務次官|常務次官]]”一職也是單獨為他創立的。海伍德自2012年1月1日以來擔任[[英國內閣秘書長|內閣秘書長]]、2014年9月以來擔任首席內務文官（Head of the Home Civil Service）<ref>{{Citation |title=Senior Appointments |url=http://www.number10.gov.uk/Page14359 |date=23 January 2008 |publisher=10 Downing Street website |accessdate=19 January 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100116001258/http://www.number10.gov.uk/Page14359 |archivedate=2010年1月16日 }}</ref><ref name=CO_0002>{{cite web |url=http://download.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/organogram/co-organogram.pdf |title=Cabinet Office Structure Charts |publisher=[[Cabinet_Office|Cabinet Office]] HM Government |date=May 2010 |accessdate=5 September 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100705004000/http://download.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/organogram/co-organogram.pdf |archivedate=2010年7月5日 }}</ref>。2017年6月被诊断出患有癌症，因此在次年6月病休，2018年10月24日因病离职<ref name="retire">[https://www.gov.uk/government/news/statement-on-sir-jeremy-heywood Statement on Sir Jeremy Heywood] {{Wayback|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/statement-on-sir-jeremy-heywood |date=20201109013548 }}, gov.uk, 24 October 2018</ref>，同年11月4日去世<ref>{{cite web | title=Former Cabinet Secretary Sir Jeremy Heywood dies from cancer at 56 | url=https://www.itv.com/news/2018-11-04/sir-jeremy-heywood-dies-from-cancer/ | website=ITV News | accessdate=4 November 2018 | archive-date=2018-11-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181104125905/https://www.itv.com/news/2018-11-04/sir-jeremy-heywood-dies-from-cancer/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=bbc>{{cite news |title=Ex-civil service chief Sir Jeremy Heywood dies |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-46089019 |work=BBC News |date=4 November 2018 |accessdate=2018-11-05 |archive-date=2020-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130174700/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-46089019 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

